'''Aurélien Djani Tchouaméni''' ({{IPA|fr|oʁeljɛ̃ dʒani tʃuameni, tʃwa-}}<!--This is an IPA transcription based on the actual pronunciation and following [[MOS:PRON]] and [[H:IPA-FR]]. Please do not remove it.-->; born 27 January 2000) is a French professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[defensive midfielder]] or a [[centre-back]] for {{Spanish football updater|Real Madrid}} club [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] and the [[France national football team|France national team]].

==Early life==
Tchouaméni was born in [[Rouen]], Normandy,<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/FootballFicheJoueur66676.html |title=Aurélien Tchouaméni |newspaper=L'Équipe |location=Paris |access-date=6 September 2021 |language=fr |archive-date=6 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220606211924/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/FootballFicheJoueur66676.html |url-status=live }}</ref> and grew up in [[Bordeaux]], [[Gironde]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.onzemondial.com/ligue-1/exclu-aurelien-tchouameni-interview-formation-bordeaux-174108 |title=Exclu – Aurélien Tchouaméni (1/2) : " J'étais le premier fan de mon papa " |newspaper=Onze Mondial |location=Paris |access-date=9 September 2021 |language=fr |archive-date=31 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220531233807/https://www.onzemondial.com/ligue-1/exclu-aurelien-tchouameni-interview-formation-bordeaux-174108 |url-status=live }}</ref> He is of [[Cameroon]]ian descent.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.camerounweb.com/CameroonHomePage/NewsArchive/Mercato-un-jeune-Camerounais-de-17ans-signe-au-Fc-Bordeaux-425931?channel=A1 |title=Mercato: un jeune Camerounais de 17ans signe au Fc Bordeaux |date=13 November 2017 |access-date=26 July 2018 |archive-date=11 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210411144224/https://www.camerounweb.com/CameroonHomePage/NewsArchive/Mercato-un-jeune-Camerounais-de-17ans-signe-au-Fc-Bordeaux-425931?channel=A1 |url-status=live }}</ref> He acquired [[French nationality law|French nationality]] on 19 December 2000 through the collective effect of his parents' [[naturalization]].<ref>{{Cite web |title=JORF n° 0296 du 22 décembre 2000 – Légifrance |url=https://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/jorf/jo/id/JORFCONT000000006652 |access-date=2 November 2023 |website=legifrance.gouv.fr |page=97 |language=fr |format=PDF}}</ref>

==Club career==
===Bordeaux===
[[File:Aurélien Tchouaméni.jpg|thumb|upright|Tchouaméni playing for [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Bordeaux]] in 2018]]

Tchouaméni made his first-team debut for [[FC Girondins de Bordeaux|Bordeaux]] in a 1–0 [[2018–19 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]] away win to Latvian side [[FK Ventspils|Ventspils]] in the second qualifying round on 26 July 2018, starting the match and playing 89 minutes.<ref name="soccerway1">{{cite web |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2018/07/26/europe/uefa-cup/futbola-klubs-ventspils/fc-girondins-de-bordeaux/2800295/ |title=Ventspils vs. Bordeaux – 26 July 2018 |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |accessdate=26 July 2018 |archive-date=11 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210411171757/https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2018/07/26/europe/uefa-cup/futbola-klubs-ventspils/fc-girondins-de-bordeaux/2800295/ |url-status=live }}</ref> He scored his first goal of his senior club career on 9 August, netting the final goal in Bordeaux's 3–1 Europa League away victory over [[FC Mariupol|Mariupol]].<ref name="soccerway2">{{cite web |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2018/08/09/europe/uefa-cup/fc-illychivets-mariupol/fc-girondins-de-bordeaux/2855297/ |title=Mariopul vs. Bordeaux – 9 August 2018 |website=Soccerway |publisher=Perform Group |accessdate=9 August 2018 |archive-date=11 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210411171752/https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2018/08/09/europe/uefa-cup/fc-illychivets-mariupol/fc-girondins-de-bordeaux/2855297/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Monaco===
On 29 January 2020, Tchouaméni signed a four-and-a-half-year deal with [[Ligue 1]] side [[AS Monaco FC|Monaco]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Aurelien-tchouameni-quitte-bordeaux-et-signe-a-monaco-jusqu-en-2024-officiel/1104163 |title=Aurélien Tchouaméni quitte Bordeaux et signe à Monaco jusqu'en 2024 (officiel) |website=L'Équipe |accessdate=31 January 2020 |archive-date=11 April 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210411171752/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Aurelien-tchouameni-quitte-bordeaux-et-signe-a-monaco-jusqu-en-2024-officiel/1104163 |url-status=live }}</ref> After almost a year playing for the club, he registered his first league goal, netting the second goal in a 3–1 win against [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]] on 23 January 2021.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ligue1.com/match?matchId=68293 |title=AS Monaco 3–1 OM |publisher=Ligue 1 |date=23 January 2021 |access-date=16 May 2021 |archive-date=27 May 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210527210900/https://www.ligue1.com/match?matchId=68293 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 14 May 2022, he delivered an assist for his captain [[Wissam Ben Yedder]] and, thus, participated in the ninth win in a row for his side.<ref>{{Cite web |date=14 May 2022 |title="Captain Wissam" et l'AS Monaco font leur festival face à Brest |url=https://www.asmonaco.com/captain-wissam-et-las-monaco-font-leur-festival-face-a-brest/ |access-date=17 May 2022 |publisher=AS Monaco FC |language=fr |archive-date=14 May 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220514221122/https://www.asmonaco.com/captain-wissam-et-las-monaco-font-leur-festival-face-a-brest/ |url-status=live }}</ref>

===Real Madrid===
On 11 June 2022, it was announced that Tchouaméni would be transferred to [[La Liga]] side [[Real Madrid CF|Real Madrid]] on 1 July 2022, signing a six-year contract with the club.<ref>{{cite web |title=Official Announcement: Tchouaméni |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2022/06/11/official-announcement-tchouameni |publisher=Real Madrid CF |date=11 June 2022 |access-date=11 June 2022 |archive-date=25 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220625122254/https://www.realmadrid.com/en/news/2022/06/11/official-announcement-tchouameni |url-status=live }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Official Statement |url=https://www.asmonaco.com/en/communique-officiel-aurelien-tchouameni/ |publisher=AS Monaco FC |date=11 June 2022 |access-date=11 June 2022 |archive-date=11 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220611114331/https://www.asmonaco.com/en/communique-officiel-aurelien-tchouameni/ |url-status=live }}</ref> The transfer fee was reported to be €80&nbsp;million, which could rise to €100&nbsp;million due to additional fees.<ref>{{cite web |title=Aurelien Tchouameni: Real Madrid sign midfielder from Monaco |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/61742709 |website=BBC Sport |date=11 June 2022 |access-date=11 June 2022 |archive-date=11 June 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20220611130504/https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/61742709 |url-status=live }}</ref>

He made his official debut for the club on 10 August, coming on as a late substitute in a 2–0 win over [[Eintracht Frankfurt]] in the [[2022 UEFA Super Cup|UEFA Super Cup]] to win his first career club trophy.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bysouth|first=Alex|title=Real Madrid 2–0 Eintracht Frankfurt: Karim Benzema scores 324th goal for Real in Super Cup win
|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/62475679|publisher=BBC|date=10 August 2022|access-date=30 September 2023}}</ref> On 30 September 2023, Tchouaméni scored his first goal for ''Los Blancos'', a header in a 3–0 league away win over [[Girona FC|Girona]].<ref>{{Cite web|title=Girona 0–3 Real Madrid: Jude Bellingham on target as visitors go top of La Liga|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/66973253|publisher=BBC|date=30 September 2023|access-date=30 September 2023}}</ref>

On 7 May 2026, Tchouaméni and teammate [[Federico Valverde]] got into a fight after a training session.<ref>{{Cite web |last= |date=7 May 2026 |title=Real Madrid's Federico Valverde taken to hospital after second Aurélien Tchouaméni fight - sources |url=https://www.espn.co.uk/football/story/_/id/48703097/real-madrid-federico-valverde-taken-hospital-second-aurelien-tchouameni-fight-sources |access-date=7 May 2026 |website=[[ESPN.com]] |language=en}}</ref> Valverde reportedly needed stitches and was brought to the hospital after getting cut during the altercation. Further on, after striking his head, Valverde experienced partial memory loss and was discovered by his teammates on the ground, drenched in blood and half-conscious.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Díaz |first=José Félix |last2=López |first2=Sergio |date=7 May 2026 |title=How the Valverde-Tchouaméni fight unfolded: accusations, punch, Fede in a wheelchair |url=https://en.as.com/soccer/how-the-valverde-tchouameni-fight-unfolded-f202605-n/ |access-date=7 May 2026 |website=AS USA |language=en-us}}</ref> Subsequent to the altercation, Real Madrid initiated a disciplinary investigation. The process concluded in both players extending mutual apologies to each other. As a result, the club imposed a fine of €500 thousand on each player and formally concluded the internal inquiry.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Comunicado Oficial |url=https://www.realmadrid.com/es-ES/noticias/club/comunicados/comunicado-oficial-07-05-2026 |access-date=7 May 2026 |website=[[Real Madrid]]}}</ref>

==International career==
On 26 August 2021, Tchouaméni received his first call up to the [[France national football team|France]] senior squad.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fff.fr/article/3280-la-liste-des-vingt-trois-bleus.html |title=La liste des vingt-trois Bleus |publisher=French Football Federation |date=26 August 2021 |access-date=26 August 2021|language=fr|archive-date=26 August 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210826143014/https://www.fff.fr/article/3280-la-liste-des-vingt-trois-bleus.html |url-status=live }}</ref> On 1 September, he made his international debut in a [[2022 FIFA World Cup qualification|2022 FIFA World Cup qualifying]] game against [[Bosnia and Herzegovina national football team|Bosnia and Herzegovina]] replacing [[Thomas Lemar]] in the 46th minute.<ref>{{cite web|first=Ben|last=McAleer|url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/who-scored-blog/2021/oct/13/aurelien-tchouameni-exciting-rise-monaco-france |title=The rise of the Monaco and France midfielder Aurélien Tchouaméni |website=The Guardian |date=13 October 2021 |access-date=11 December 2022 |archive-date=11 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221211004310/https://www.theguardian.com/football/who-scored-blog/2021/oct/13/aurelien-tchouameni-exciting-rise-monaco-france |url-status=live }}</ref> On 25 March 2022, Tchouaméni scored his first goal for the national team in a [[Friendly (association football)|friendly]] against [[Ivory Coast national football team|Ivory Coast]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.besoccer.com/new/france-2-1-ivory-coast-tchouameni-completes-late-turnaround-for-les-bleus-1119478 |title=France 2–1 Ivory Coast: Tchouameni completes late turnaround for Les Bleus |website=BeSoccer |date=25 March 2022 |access-date=11 December 2022 |archive-date=11 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221211004316/https://www.besoccer.com/new/france-2-1-ivory-coast-tchouameni-completes-late-turnaround-for-les-bleus-1119478 |url-status=live }}</ref>

In November 2022, Tchouaméni was named in France's squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Bleus-une-liste-de-25-pour-la-coupe-du-monde-avec-giroud-mandanda-et-saliba/1364022 |title=Bleus : une liste de 25 pour la Coupe du monde avec Giroud, Mandanda et Saliba |trans-title=A 25-player list for the World Cup with Giroud, Mandanda and Saliba |newspaper=L'Équipe |language=fr |date=9 November 2022 |access-date=9 November 2022 |archive-date=14 November 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221114210253/https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Actualites/Bleus-une-liste-de-25-pour-la-coupe-du-monde-avec-giroud-mandanda-et-saliba/1364022 |url-status=live }}</ref> On 10 December, he scored his first World Cup goal in a 2–1 victory over [[England national football team|England]] in the quarter-finals.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.goal.com/en/news/france-tchouameni-england-world-cup-quarter-final/bltfa47e4a95acb36f8 |title=Watch: France star Tchouameni smashes long-range strike past England in World Cup quarter-final |website=Goal |date=10 December 2022 |access-date=11 December 2022 |archive-date=11 December 2022 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20221211004310/https://www.goal.com/en/news/france-tchouameni-england-world-cup-quarter-final/bltfa47e4a95acb36f8 |url-status=live }}</ref>

On 18 December 2022, Tchouaméni started in the [[2022 FIFA World Cup Final]]. He was one of two French players to miss in the [[penalty shootout]] as France lost to [[Argentina national football team|Argentina]] at the [[Lusail Stadium]], Qatar.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://edition.cnn.com/2023/03/06/football/world-cup-final-penalty-shootout-spt-intl/index.html|title=World Cup final: How Argentina won penalty shootout|date=6 March 2023|access-date=25 November 2023|website=CNN Sports}}</ref>

